courses.subject: ENGL
courses.title: Readng & Wrtng about Lit.
courses.notes: NOTE: ENGL 1100 fulfills the new writing requirement in the Faculty of Arts at UBC.  Students entering other faculties at UBC or planning to transfer to other institutions should take ENGL 1127 or ENGL 1128 instead of ENGL 1100.Students planning to enrol in a first-semester English course must take the Langara English Test (LET) or Language Proficiency Index Test (LPI) prior to the semester in which they want to register.  Students who have BC English 12 or BC English Literature 12 or equivalent with an 80% or higher are not required to write the LET or LPI.Students not meeting those exemptions need the following scores on LET or LPI:LET 3 or LPI 26 on the essay with one of the following:5/10 or higher in sentence structure; or5/10 or higher in English usage; or10/20 or higher in reading comprehension.Students who have scored a level 3 on the LET (or 26/40 with a 5 or higher in English usage on the LPI) are also strongly encouraged to register in English 1121 (there is no tuition charge for this course for Canadian Citizens and Permanent residents) in order to upgrade their reading and writing skills.  English 1121 will help students at this prerequisite level succeed in ENGL 1127 which is the university transfer course.  See calendar for course descriptions.

courses.subject: PHYS
courses.title: Energy and the Environment
courses.notes: Langara Environment Institute 2012, Energy and the Environment, consists of three courses: PHYS 1124, HIST 2260, and INST 1105.  INST 1105 will include field trips, guest speakers, films and seminar discussions on the theme of energy and environment, and will greatly enhance the other two courses.  To develop an understanding of the technical as well as the social issues involved in the transition to a low-carbon energy future, students are encouraged to register for all three courses.  Questions may be directed to instructors Robin Macqueen  rmacqueen@langara.bc.ca or  Craig Keating  ckeating@langara.bc.ca
